R-Car Gen3 GPIO Driver testing program
-----------------------------------------

Usage:
    #rcar-gpio -gX & : must be running

    Syntax:
        #gpio_test device=<device path> port=<port pin> value=<value> mode=<mode>

        Options
            - <device path> = /dev/gpioX
            - <port pin>    =  0..31 of port X
            - <value>       =  0 or 1
            - <mode>        =  <mode>[:<posneg>][:<edglevel>][:<bothedge>]
                               - <mode>     =  in  :      Input mode
                                               out :      Output mode
                                               int :      Interrupt mode
                               - <posneg>   =  pos :      Positive logic
                                               neg :      Negative logic
                               - <edglevel> =  edg :      Edge detection interrupt
                                               lev :      Level dectection interrupt
                               - <bothedg>  =  bot :      Both Edge detection interrupt
                                               one :      Falling/Rising Edge detection interrrupt
                                      

Examples:
==================================================
For V3H Condor/V3M Eagle board:
Start GPIO driver:
    #rcar-gpio -g5

Check status on pins (GP5_12, GP5_13 and GP5_14)
1) Check LED3, LED4 and LED5
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=12 mode=out value=0    // LED3 (GP5_12)on V3H cpu_board: Dark
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=13 mode=out value=0    // LED4 (GP5_13)on V3H cpu_board: Dark
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=14 mode=out value=0    // LED5 (GP5_14)on V3H cpu_board: Dark

    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=12 mode=out value=1    // LED3 (GP5_12)on V3H cpu_board: Light
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=13 mode=out value=1    // LED4 (GP5_13)on V3H cpu_board: Light
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=14 mode=out value=1    // LED5 (GP5_14)on V3H cpu_board: Light

    
2) Check SW15, SW16 and SW17

    - No press SW15/SW16/SW17 on V3H cpu_board, read status on terminal is 1 
    - Press and hold SW15/SW16/SW17 on V3H cpu_board, read status on terminal is 0  
    
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=12 mode=in              // SW15 on V3H/V3M cpu_board.
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=13 mode=in              // SW16 on V3H/V3M cpu_board.
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio5 port=14 mode=in              // SW17 on V3H/V3M cpu_board.

