For D3 Draak
Start GPIO driver:
    #rcar-gpio -g1
    #rcar-gpio -g4

Check status on pins (GP4_07, GP4_25 and GP1_30)
1) Check LED12, LED13 and LED14
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio1 port=30 mode=out value=0    // LED12 (GP1_30) on D3 Draak cpu_board: Dark
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio4 port=7 mode=out value=0     // LED13 (GP4_07) on D3 Draak cpu_board: Dark
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio4 port=25 mode=out value=0    // LED14 (GP4_25) on D3 Draak cpu_board: Dark

    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio1 port=30 mode=out value=1    // LED12 (GP1_30) on D3 Draak cpu_board: Light
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio4 port=7 mode=out value=1     // LED13 (GP4_07) on D3 Draak cpu_board: Light
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio4 port=25 mode=out value=1    // LED14 (GP4_25) on D3 Draak cpu_board: Light

    Note: Can't write 0 or 1 to GP4_07, so can't check LED13
    
2) Check SW57, SW58 and SW59

    - No press SW57/SW58/SW59 on D3 Draak cpu_board, read status on terminal is 1 
    - Press and hold SW57/SW58/SW59 on D3 Draak cpu_board, read status on terminal is 0  
    
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio1 port=30 mode=in              // SW58 on D3 Draak cpu_board.
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio4 port=7 mode=in               // SW59 on D3 Draak cpu_board.
    #gpio_test device=/dev/gpio4 port=25 mode=in              // SW57 on D3 Draak cpu_board.
    
